        "id": "1670408347989559118",
        "text": "Circular buffers are not tricks. They are the correct data structure when you cannot allocate.\n\n```c\nstruct ring {\n    uint8_t buf[256];\n    uint8_t head;\n};\n#define PUSH(r, v) ((r).buf[++(r).head] = (v))\n```\n\nNo malloc. No free. No fragmentation. One byte of state. Viking-era...",
